                  <li><p> The limit does not exist because the function is oscillating between -1 and 1.</p></li>
                  <li><p> The limit does not exist because you are dividing by zero when <m>x = 0</m> for <m>f(x).</m></p></li>
                </ol>
              </p>
            </statement>
